									"patching_rect" : [ 442.0, 294.0, 297.0, 248.0 ],
									"text" : "instructions: send a bunch of lightChannel messages to the left inlet of the v8 object. The first thing to send  is the light number; this  corresponds to this patch's inlets: here just four, for controlling four lights. But each of these lights can have an arbitrary DMX strarting channel (lights should be in 4-channel RGB+White mode, or whatever else, as long as you have the starting channel (first four channels are usually RGB+W no matter which mode, or so I'm told).\n\nThe RGB lists arriving from the four inlets range from 0-255; these will be mapped to the given lights via the correct channels. \n\nNB we always send out one complete DMX universe i.e. 512 channels\n\nm@michael-edwards.org ~ 2nd September 2025"
								}

